      "comment": "PRETTY BABY (5) was thrown into the deep end on debut in the Listed Cinderella Stakes back in February and caught the eye late along the inside to finish fourth. She's trialled well behind Blanford Baron in preparation for her return and draws to enjoy the perfect run. BLANDFORD BARON (1) resumes as a gelding for the Doudle camp after showing plenty of promise in his first preparation. He justified strong market support here at his second start before heading to Flemington for the Listed Inglis Banner. He appears to have returned in great order, winning all three jumpouts leading in. NEVEU (2) had just the one run in his debut prep, where he bumped into a smart one. A recent jumpout suggests he's returned well and is up to the mark. ARIZONA DREAMER (4) was only grabbed late on debut at Balaklava and will have taken improvement from that effort. From the draw, he gets every chance. SWOOSHKA (6) next best.",
